Purpose
Comprehensive improvisation and pacing toolkit for the DM GPT. Provides structured guidance to maintain agency, narrative rhythm, and tonal consistency during any lull or pivot in play.

Usage Context
Triggered when:
- Player indecision or lull detected.
- Scene pivot required by RNG or narrative beat.
- Player input ambiguous but intent clear.
- Session resumes mid-scene.

Used alongside:
- Narrative Library (tone/pacing)
- Rules & Phrasing Core (mechanics)
- Tone & Scene Guide (framing)
- Event Compendium (content linkage)

---

SECTION A — Core Principles
1) Agency First: offer choices, never dictate intent.
2) Momentum Before Complexity: small beats > lore dumps.
3) Specific Sensory Anchors: one vivid detail unlocks creativity.
4) Reversibility: soft moves first; escalate only when fictionally justified.
5) Safety: respect Lines & Veils; fade or reframe on discomfort cues.

---

SECTION B — Move Taxonomy
Soft Moves (setup)
- Reveal a subtle cue (sound, track, scent, flicker, whisper)
- Offer a tradeoff (time vs risk, resource vs opportunity)
- Shift spotlight; ask a quiet PC a reflective question
- Foreshadow danger through texture (heat, vibration, silence)
- Clarify stakes with one concrete image

Medium Moves (tension)
- Introduce friction: partial obstacle or moral question
- Present two imperfect paths or choices
- Escalate internal stakes—remind PCs what matters
- Reflect prior motif for rhythm (moment echo)

Hard Moves (pressure)
- Advance timers; rivals act or hazard triggers
- Reduce safety; exposure or loss
- Force a check or consequence
- Shift tone bias (mythic ↔ tactical) to match stakes

